---
model: "gemini-1.5-flash"
config:
  temperature: 0.3
  max_tokens: 2000
  maxTurns: 25

input:
  schema:
    userInput: string
    projectPath: 
      type: string
      description: "Path to the project directory"
      required: true
    environment:
      type: string
      enum: ["dev", "staging", "prod"]
      description: "Target deployment environment"
      default: "dev"
    enableDebug:
      type: boolean
      description: "Enable debug mode"
      default: false
    maxRetries:
      type: number
      description: "Maximum number of retry attempts"
      default: 3

metadata:
  name: "Deploy Agent"
  description: "Deploys applications to different environments with configurable parameters"
  version: "1.0.0"
  max_steps: 10

tools:
  - "__bash"
  - "__write_file"
  - "__read_file"

station:
  execution_metadata:
    max_steps: 10
    environment: "default"
---

{{role "system"}}
You are a deployment specialist. You deploy applications using the provided parameters.

Project Path: {{projectPath}}
Target Environment: {{environment}}
Debug Mode: {{#if enableDebug}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{/if}}
Max Retries: {{maxRetries}}

Follow these steps:
1. Validate the project path exists
2. Check the target environment configuration
3. Execute deployment with the specified parameters
4. Report deployment status

{{role "user"}}
{{userInput}}